title: Woodblock [zinc-faced], "Lady with Parisol under a Trellis", ca. 1880
medium: wood, with incised sheet zinc facing, fastened by brads
description: vertical rectangle - an oriental lady with a parisol stands under a wooden trellis, over which vines are growing and which is approached by a flight of stairs, left - all in the "style chinois".

tombstone.epitaph: Woodblock [zinc-faced], "Lady with Parisol under a Trellis", ca. 1880.wood, with incised sheet zinc facing, fastened by brads. Gift of Anonymous Donor. a-d-330.
